This paper belongs to the field of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on Sentiment Analysis. The paper uses lexical resources and supervised learning techniques to classify text based on the sentiments of the author. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. 

The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as supervised learning, to train the model. This makes it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and classification of text, which makes it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). 

Therefore, the 5 likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely, are: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY.
